    "story":  [
                  "Lording it at the top, \u003cb\u003eQuince\u003c/b\u003e is boring everyone into an early grave \u0026mdash; 6 clean sheets, zero entertainment. The kind of football that makes people emigrate. Smugly in tow, \u003cb\u003eSid\u003c/b\u003e has turned the goalless draw into an art form nobody asked for \u0026mdash; 6 of them. A black hole where fun goes to die. Rounding out the insufferable elite, \u003cb\u003eBig Pewerk\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s lot defend like the door\u0027s been left on the latch, but they\u0027ll at least outscore the misery \u0026mdash; 28 goals (GD +1), led by Netherlands (beautiful football, then a fistfight among themselves). Thrilling, doomed.",
                  "Wallowing in mid-table sludge, \u003cb\u003eIke\u003c/b\u003e saw something in Uzbekistan (the tournament\u0027s great unmarked mystery box) that no scout, coach or sane human ever has \u0026mdash; played, did nothing, and is somehow still the jewel of that abysmal squad. Equally forgettable, \u003cb\u003eEllie\u003c/b\u003e\u0027s defence is a public health hazard \u0026mdash; 28 shipped, Qatar (lavishly funded, modestly threatening) leaking 10 of them. Genuinely embarrassing to be associated with. Barely clinging to relevance, \u003cb\u003eEtan\u003c/b\u003e will be replaying Senegal (power, pace and swagger for days)\u0027s 5-0 all tournament because, let\u0027s be honest, it\u0027s the only good thing their team will ever do. Frame it.",
                  "Down in the dregs, \u003cb\u003eMurray\u003c/b\u003e had to sit and watch New Zealand (the All Whites: good time, not a long time) get battered 1-5 \u0026mdash; and we\u0027ll be bringing it up at every opportunity for the rest of their natural life. And scraping the very bottom of the barrel, \u003cb\u003eElsa\u003c/b\u003e spread their picks out of sheer cowardice \u0026mdash; 4 teams all contributing scraps, not one brave enough to actually be good. Death by committee."
              ],
